
[1]magnetize

   MAG'NETIZE, v.t. To communicate magnetic properties to any thing; as,
   to magnetize a needle.

   Seven of Deslon's patients were magnetized at Dr. Franklin's house.

   MAG'NETIZE, v.i. To acquire magnetic properties; to become magnetic. A
   bar of iron standing some time in an inclined position, will magnetize.
